As of the 2010 census, there were 428 people living in the CDP: 226 male and 202 female. 93 were 19 years old or younger, 21 were ages 20–34, 80 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 163 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 71 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 51.9 years.

The racial makeup of the CDP was 90.9% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 1.2% [[Race (United States Census)|Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander]], 0.7% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 0.7% [[Race (United States Census)|Black or African American]], 0.5% [[Race (United States Census)|American Indian or Alaska Native]], 3.0% [[Race (United States Census)|Other]], and 3.0% [[Race (United States Census)|Two or More Races]].  4.9% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 169 households in the CDP, 147 family households (87%) and 22 non-family households (13%), with an average household size of 2.53. Of the family households, 138 were married couples living together, while 7 were single fathers and 2 were single mothers; the non-family households included 16 adults living alone: 10 male and 6 female.

The CDP contained 194 housing units, of which 169 were occupied and 25 were vacant.<ref name=GR2>{{cite web |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0440400 |title=American FactFinder: Lazy Y U CDP, Arizona |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=December 10, 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213055035/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0440400 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 }}</ref>

